  "title": "M&E ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for all on-site technical and engineering matters.</li>\n  <li>Determines project schedule by monitoring project progress, coordinating activities, and resolving site problems.</li>\n  <li>Prepares project status reports.</li>\n  <li>Coordinates structural details and design features within the project.</li>\n  <li>Flexible and able to work well in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Ensure works are carried out to meet the Company's quality standard and contractual requirements.</li>\n  <li>Supervise the M &amp; E works and coordinate with client’s representatives, consultants and sub-contractors technical matters.</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely and smooth progress of works.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Diploma/Degree in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Must be 5 years of working experience in the building construction industry preferably with school/government projects.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in AutoCAD/BIM Modelling.</li>\n  <li>Organized, highly motivated, and independent with excellent team spirit and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Piority will be for immediate hiring. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Competitive remuneration package commensurate with qualifications will be offered.</strong></p>\n<p>Interested candidates are invited to apply via email with an updated resume, which should include current and expected salaries, date of availability, and a recent photograph in MS Word Format. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>Thank you for applying.</p>",
